Methods in java
    Are blocks of code which contains some java statements. whenever we
    call a method, those statements are executed. Methods have names
    we use these names to call them.
String Class:
    Upside:
        It is designed to save space.
    Downside:
        It is immutable (not changeable) and slow.
StringBuilder:
    Upside:
        It is fast and changeable.
    Downside:
        Not optimized for space-saving.